This paper focuses on video analysis and action recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also introduces a new method for compressing video frames to save transmission bandwidth, which involves training a neural network, indicating a focus on machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of mobile devices, suggesting a potential focus on multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also involves end-to-end training with 3D CNNs, indicating a potential focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper involves extensive experiments to evaluate the proposed method, suggesting a potential focus on neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE).
